
[1]anxious

   ANX'IOUS, a ank'shus.

   1. Greatly concerned or solicitous, respecting something future or
   unknown; being in painful suspense; applied to persons; as, to be
   anxious for the issue of a battle.

   2. Full of solicitude; unquiet; applied to things; as anxious thoughts
   or labor.

   3. Very careful; solicitous; as, anxious to please; anxious to commit
   no mistake.

   It is followed by for or about, before the object.
